{
  "texts": [
    "Thanks to the prior knowledge learning of neural networks, the original complete shape can be restored from the local shape.",
    "However, the completion strongly relies on the prior knowledge brought by the training set, which brings challenges to the type and quantity of data, and also brings great limitations to the popularization and generalization of the method.",
    "At the same time, due to the fuzziness of the completion task itself, the registration without overlapping is also complicated.",
    "To deal with the influence of non-overlapping regions on registration results, researchers conducted a series of studies from the positive and negative directions of removing and predicting the addition of non-overlapping regions.",
    "The method of eliminating the non-overlapping area can theoretically be applied to the various methods of complete overlap in order to deal with partial overlap."
  ]
}